@node Preface
@chapter Preface

ELOT --- the @emph{Emacs Literate Ontology Tool} --- is a package for
authoring OWL ontologies in Org-mode.  A single Org file is both the
ontology source (tangled to OWL Manchester Syntax) and the published
documentation (exported to HTML@comma{} PDF@comma{} or Info).

@menu
* Who this manual is for::
* How to read this manual::
* Conventions::
* Getting help::
@end menu

@node Who this manual is for
@section Who this manual is for

@itemize
@item
@strong{Ontology authors} who want their ontology and its documentation to
stay in sync@comma{} automatically.
@item
@strong{Emacs users} curious about how literate programming applies to
knowledge engineering.
@item
@strong{Newcomers to OWL} who want a working ontology in front of them
before reading a 400-page semantic-web textbook.
@end itemize

No prior experience with OWL or Org-mode is assumed for Part I@.
Parts II--IV assume you have completed the tutorial.

@node How to read this manual
@section How to read this manual

This manual follows the @uref{https://diataxis.fr/, Diátaxis} structure:

@itemize
@item
Read @ref{Part I --- Tutorial, , Part I} front-to-back the first time.
@item
Dip into @ref{Part II --- How-to guides, , Part II} when you have a specific task.
@item
Consult @ref{Part III --- Reference, , Part III} for lookups.
@item
Read @ref{Part IV --- Background, , Part IV} when you want to know @emph{why}.
@end itemize

